article.description: Jordan Washington scored 21 points and Deyshonee Much added 19 in Iona's 101-66 dismantling of Marist Friday night.
article.headline: Washington leads the way in Iona's 101-66 win over Marist
article.linkText: Washington leads the way in Iona's 101-66 win over Marist
article.story: POUGHKEEPSIE, N.Y. -- Jordan Washington scored 21 points and Deyshonee Much added 19 in Iona's 101-66 dismantling of Marist Friday night. Washington, Much and Isaiah Williams-who scored 18 points-combined to shoot 22 for 32 from the floor. Iona (3-2, 2-0 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference) shot 63.3 percent from the floor. A.J. English scored 16 points and had nine assists, six rebounds, three steals and three blocked shots for the Gaels. Khallid Hart scored 18 points and Brian Parker 16 for Marist (1-4, 0-1). The Red Foxes shot 38 percent from the floor. Williams' 3-pointer with 14:27 until intermission gave the Gaels a 12-11 lead they would never relinquish. Williams hit another 3 24 seconds later, and in less than five minutes Iona raced to a 29-13 lead with 9:42 before the break. Iona recorded nine 3 pointers in the first half and led Marist 52-26 at halftime.
